to the spires<br><br>2. I gated when I did it, others have sworn that you should follow her out. /shrug who knows?<br><br>3. He runs due east, just outside the fort wall, towards EW.<br><br>Tat <p>Tatanka WolfDancer, 59th Druid<BR>Silvara Drakonsbane, 48th Druid<BR>Bigith Dwigus, 48th Warrior<BR>Snookims Whinzlow, 44th Enchanter<BR>Ethereal, 7th Hammer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzaarain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Za Arain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#333399>(5/9/02 12:09:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5296.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromriff Legs Question</span><hr size=1> I ran back to the fort but didn't follow the broodmama around.  She takes her time getting there.  And will dance around near the entrance teasing you before she actually goes for it.  Be patient and don't jump the gun.<br><br>-Gruffydd<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubremen7.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bremen7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#333399>(5/9/02 5:02:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5296.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromriff Legs Question</span><hr size=1> And tell your group not to engage Fergul and Gray until the BM gets there. The Fergul that comes running to the entrance is NOT the one. Until the BM starts the script and pops the &quot;running Fergul&quot; you shouldn't do anything. <br><br>Once he starts hauling ass Eastwards, THEN you snag him. If he gets to the EW zone line he poofs and you've failed. Watch out for adds.  <br><br>I would walk the BM to the entrance of the fort to keep others from interfering or to make sure nothing goes wrong. <br><br>FF has about 8-9k Hp's if memory serves. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uguluvasea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>guluvasea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333399>(5/9/02 6:05:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5296.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromriff Legs Question</span><hr size=1> when i got my military leggings i solo'd the quest was in my forties...i bound my self to the edge of the fort that faces to the stream in the front...<br><br>i then got into the caves (had to weave in and out) while invissed and was able to make my way to the bm and handed in the control harness..she took off and i gate back ( i did make sure the zone was aware what was going on)<br><br>had to wait a minute or two and watched the two guards come out and wait at their posts...the bm showed up and attacke the other one and killed him, then she attacked fergy.<br><br>i immediately entered the fray and both attacked me...no prob i headed back to the druid circle with fergy in tow with the bm following way behind  she is slow  when we got farenough out that she lost aggro it was time to snare root and dot fergy...which did not take too long and walaa! i got my leggings.<br><br>good luck!<br>dekkon fuzzyfeet<br>lvl 57 halfing druid<br>inoruuk server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utimik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>timik</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.dork.com/brak211/timiksmileyicon.bmp" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333399>(5/10/02 1:50:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5296.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromriff Legs Question</span><hr size=1> i've never actually done the quest, but i have legs.  about a year ago great divide was bugged and BM kept making the walk w/o being given the harness, and fergul would pop and run.  it was great we got about 20 pairs of leggings. <p><central><img src="http://www.dork.com/brak211/timiksig.JPG"><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=128240">View My Inventory @ Magelo</a></central></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukytelae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kytelae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Love the Grove</span><br>  Posts: 1134<br> <font color=#333399>(5/10/02 2:12:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5296.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.river.org/~jnfr/EQ/mtg.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromriff Legs Question</span><hr size=1> I thought this quest was still broken. Can someone confirm that it's working again? <p><b>Bittleaye Arkades</b><br><i> Halfling Druid of Xev</i><br>Sans Requiem</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pu